│ The problem is that the code assumes `Order[Idx]` is always < `Sz` when it's not equal to `Sz`, but this assumption can be violated. To fix this, we need to add a bounds check       │
│ before calling `UsedIndices.set()`.                                                                                                                                                   │
│                                                                                                                                                                                       │
│ Looking at the logic, if `Order[Idx] >= Sz`, it should probably be treated the same as `Order[Idx] == Sz` (i.e., ignored for the UsedIndices marking). Let me implement this fix.     │
│                                                                                                                                                                                       │
│ ```bash                                                                                                                                                                               │
│ sed -i '5930s/if (Order\[Idx\] != Sz)/if (Order[Idx] != Sz && Order[Idx] < Sz)/' /llvm-autofix-deps/llvm/llvm/llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/SLPVectorizer.cpp                         │
│ ```                                                                                                                                                                                   │
